  Non-Profit Organizations WWW Sites related to Microscopy & Microanalysis
     __________________________________________________________________

   This list provides you with links to additional Non-Profit Organization
   WWW sites which are involved in Microscopy/Microanalysis across the
   world.
     __________________________________________________________________

  Sites in the United States of America
     __________________________________________________________________

     * American Crystallographic Association
     * American Microscopical Society
     * International Field Emission Society (IFES)
     * International Cement Microscopy Association
     * Optical Society of America
     * Protein Data Bank (PDB)
     * Links for Chemists
     * Advanced Electron Microscopy and Imaging at House Ear Institute,
       Los Angeles, California, USA
     * OpticalImaging Association (OPIA)
     * Poor Vacuum SEM User Resources
     * Immunocytochemistry Newsgroup
     __________________________________________________________________

  Sites in Europe
     __________________________________________________________________

     * Historical microscopes, Museum of Physics,University of Naples
     * International Union of Crystallography
     * Cambridge Structural Database (CSD)
     * Inorganic Crystal Structure Database
     * Metals Crystallographic Data File (CRYSTMET)
     * The World-Wide Web Virtual Library: Crystallography
     * EM Yellow Pages
     * Microscopes and Microscopy Chris Jefferies WWW Site in the UK
     * The Quekett Microscopical Club London, UK
     * Microscopy-UK Home of Amateur Microscopy in the UK
     * Nederlandse Vereniging voor Microscopie
     * Dutch site for pathology technichians
     * Russian Society of Scanning Probe Microscopy and Nanotechnology
     * Royal microscopical society
     * Sechenov Inst. for Evolutional Biochemistry and Physiology Rus.
       Acad. Sci.
     * Fun Science Gallery, Bologna, Italy
     __________________________________________________________________

  Sites in Australia, Asia, Africa & South Pacific
     __________________________________________________________________

     * Microscopy Society of Southern Africa (MSSA)
